sooty shearwater
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a variety of puffin of southern oceans whose young are eaten as muttonbird. See also MUTTONBIRD. [shearwater, from its habit of skimming the water surface]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:muttonbird, titi
